\b How content is moving from Amplience to SFCC explain in detail?\par

\pard{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf1\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b0 When an edition is scheduled in the Dynamic Content app, a webhook_event is generated.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The webhook service will notify the integration and send it a "payload" containing information about the edition.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The integration will use this edition data to create a campaign in SFCC.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The campaign description will be set to the edition name, the campaign schedule will match the edition schedule and the campaign ID will be set to the edition ID.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}Once the campaign is created, the integration will request the HTML for each slot in the edition.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}It makes use of the \b content rendering\b0  Service to convert slot content into HTML format.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The content rendering service retrieves the slot in JSON format and converts it into HTML using a handlebars template.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}For each slot in the edition, the integration will create a slot configuration for the corresponding slot in SFCC.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The HTML contents of the slot will be stored in the slot configuration.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The slot configuration is then assigned to the SFCC campaign.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}The content is now available to be previewed in the SFCC storefront and to be scheduled to go live.\par
{\pntext\f1\'B7\tab}If you choose to unschedule the edition in Dynamic Content, then the campaign and slot configurations will be deleted.\par

\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\b What is Webhook?\par
\b0 A webhook is a way for Dynamic Content to automatically send messages or data to a third party system\b\par
What is visualization explain in detail?\par
\b0 Used to preview your content at any time during the content production process.\line User must click save to see any content changes within the  visualization.\line visualization display can be toggled on and off by clicking the eye icon at the top of the screen.\line You can use the device size menu to see how the content displays on different device screen sizes.\par
\b What are extensions in Amplience and how we can use?\par
\b0 Extensions are simple web apps that extend the functionality of Dynamic Content. There are three types of extensions:\par
\b content field extensions:- \b0 This extensions are used to extend the features of the content editing form.\b\par
content editor extensions:- \b0 This extensions augment the content editing experience and are displayed in a tab on the content form.\b\par
dashboard extensions:- \b0 This extensions are full screen extensions displayed in a tab on the dashboard.\b\par
How to configure preview in Amplience?\par
\b0 To view content previews you must have a content preview app set up and specified in the "preview settings" dialog.\b\par
